content: Nothing to add except GOOD ON YOU! Keep plugging away, bro! Do the best you can, and be the best you can! Just so you know, you can contact any recruiter and ask them for a printed ASVAB pre-test and practice test and they will provide you one at no charge. If you struggle in any area, go back and ask them for the study guide, though that is also free with a simple Google search. Here is a great site that provides both FREE exam tests and advice with feedback (remove the " from the link and copy and paste into your browser): "http://www.studyguidezone.com/asvabtest.htm" Best wishes to you!
